Adding ballot comment sections to:

update the css to class and not just p elementswrap

whole page: create page variable = for_ballot trigger page level class for content in layout

- does not work for generated html_pages

- create a list of page names for ballot in _config.yml and look up to see if for ballot:

~~~yml
ballot_pages: # list of pages to highlight for balloters/comments  names = html pages for ig pub generated artifacts and file names for pages
- index.md #page.name = source file name for "static" pages
- StructureDefinition-template-basic.html # page.name file name for ig-pub generated html_pages
~~~

{% if site.ballot_pages contains page.name %} note-to-balloters{% endif %}
 e.g.,
<body{% if site.ballot_pages contains site.page %} class="note-to-balloters"{% endif %}>

see framework/_includes/container-start.html

for actually where this is implemented

section  append {: .note-to-balloters} to kramdown blocks or <div class="note-to-balloters" markdown="1"></div>  to multiple blocks)

append {: .note-to-balloters} to next line of block element  ( p )

 or prepend to beginning of list li html element

append {: .note-to-balloters} to end of inline element (span)
